com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IRepositoryProgressMonitor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle, IRepositoryProgressMonitorHandle, ISimpleItem, ISimpleItemHandle

    public interface IRepositoryProgressMonitor
extends IRepositoryProgressMonitorHandle, ISimpleItem
    A repository progress monitor is a persistent item which allows support for cancellation in RPC style service methods. The intent is that by adding a monitor to a service method declaration the service call will automatically be cancellable and the cancellation will be handled by the framework.
    Since:
    0.6

    • Method Detail

      • setWrappedMonitor

        void setWrappedMonitor(org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
        Sets the wrapped progress monitor for this repository monitor. The wrapped monitor is transient and not sent to the server. It's meant to allow client code to track user cancellation requests and propagate them appropriately. If a wrapped monitor is not available on the client, then cancellation won't be supported.
        Parameters:
        monitor - the wrapper progress monitor for this repository monitor.

      • getWrappedMonitor

      • getState

        int getState()
        Return state of this monitor if set. The value will be one of
        • DEFAULT_RUNNING - the task is running or state has not been explicitly set
        • SCHEDULED - the task for this monitor has been scheduled for asynchronous execution
        • ASYNC - the task is running asynchronously
        • DONE - the task has completed

      • getResult

        int getResult()
        Return the result of the operation. The value may be one of
        • UNKNOWN - the result is not known or not been explicitly set
        • OK - the task completed successfully
        • WARNING - the task completed with warnings
        • ERROR - the task completed with errors
